e [ https://substack.com/redirect/c5ee8bf0-01d2-46ca-ade7-07aa318138d3?j=3D=
eyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ]:
Our vision of the Metaverse will run on the Dataverse: a composable, web-sc=
ale data ecosystem=E2=80=94owned by everyone and no one. Developers will bu=
ild interchangeable interfaces and online experiences that directly interac=
t with the Dataverse and the composable data that lives there. The Datavers=
e will play arguably the most important role within the Metaverse: a shared=
, high-performance, always-available graph of all data created and used by =
all applications.
But I think Small Apps and Protocols can focus more intentionally on their =
respective roles in the context of time. Small Apps will burn brightly and =
explode, and smart Protocols will do whatever it takes to ensure that they=
=E2=80=99re the Dyson Sphere capturing the energy in the process.
I think about it like an update of Fat Protocols, Thin Applications with a =
